dc_title_s: Map of part of the island of Newfoundland to illustrate the paper by Staff-Commander G. Robinson R.N.
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Route of the party overland from Bonne Bay to Green Bay is shown. Includes elevation profile of route [horizontal scale 1:253,440; vertical scale ca. 1:38,400]. Includes descriptions of vegetation and soil quality. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 47, (1877), pp. 278-84; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.47 1877
dc_publisher_s: London: published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1877.
